<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="1430" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1430">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/8–349: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-12T18:00:00-04:00">August 12,
                                    1949—6 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>235. Reurtel 394, Aug 3. Dept has well to fore difficult position ur
                            office and is giving entire question continuing consideration.</p>
                        <p>Pls inform what travel facilities, rail or ship, wld likely be available
                            for withdrawal Amers generally from ur district, for our reference in
                            case decision later made to close Consulate. Also report situation re
                            exit permits.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>